A hymn to Faunus as protector os the flocks and herds. The occa- sion, as the tenth verse shows, was not the great city festival of the Lupercalia on February 15, but the country celebration which fell on the 5th of December. The first two strophes contain the prayer for the god's favor3 the remaining two describe the holiday. Mene, 69.
